cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image reconstruction from highly undersampled data. The use of Bayesian nonparametric models and dictionary learning also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves optimization algorithms, which could place it in the information theory (cs.IT) or numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the use of regularization techniques and empirical results suggest that it could also belong to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
